<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25116e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25116e">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25116e"> 116(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in presence of / my mind / <font face="wake">S</font> deaf by / <font face="wake">H</font>&apos;s noise</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But as the wise men feared lest some ignorant youth should learn the name and be able to destroy the world&mdash;which God avert!&mdash;they made by magic two brazen lions, which they set before the entrance of the Holy of Holies, one on the right, the other on the left. Now, if any one were to go within and learn the holy Name, then the lions would begin to <mark>roar as he came out, so that from alarm and bewilderment he would lose his presence of mind and forget</mark> the Name. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 187</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14071e" href="c14all.htm#c14071e">VI.C.14:071(e)</a>, <a name="c14071f" href="c14all.htm#c14071f">VI.C.14:071(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
